    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for nss.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Network Security Services (NSS) is a set of libraries designed to support the cross-platform development of security-enabled client and server applications.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* nss: vulnerable to Minerva side-channel information leak (CVE-2023-6135)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
